==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noil
<hw>Noil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. Prov. E.
<ets>oil</ets>, <ets>ile</ets>, <ets>ail</ets>, a beard of grain (OE.
<ets>eil</ets>, AS. <ets>egl</ets>) combined with the indef. article,
<ets>an oil</ets> becoming <ets>a noil</ets>.]</ety> <def>A short or
waste piece or knot of wool separated from the longer staple by combing;
also, a similar piece or shred of waste silk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noils</ent>⟦br⟧
